snippet.textDisplay: I never felt hype for this game, well to be real... I never felt hype to any game at this point. They all look good at first, but than reality hits u hard. They end up unpolished mess. Full of bugs, crashes. 3 hour long main story...mhmm N F S mmh H E A T mmmgmm. How u even dare to take a legendary name as NFS, and turn it in to this. Meaningless bulshit. HOW U EVEN DARE TO CHARGE 60€ FOR THIS SHIT. Gaming industry lead to this point and there was nothing we could done to stop that. You ware the ones who bought loot boxes, u ware the ones who gamble thousands of dollars to be superior in pay to win games. Developers saw that, and abused it. Even Games That I loved and grinded so hard, eventually became Pay2Win cash grab. Like World Of Tanks, Lineage 2 ( all Mmmos in general)... That's what lead me in to this emotionless state. I just don't care anymore. Because I know how it's going to end up. Ofcs I'm not saying ALL the games are like this. Far from it. I still adore games like League Of Legends, or some FPS titles... That require PURE skill and not deep pockets.

snippet.textDisplay:
From the rules: "Design has to be based on the Alienware™ Aurora™ R9 personal computer".


And:
"In the course of the building stage, the Teams must refrain from the following changes of the original"

Alienware™ Aurora™ R9 personal computer:
a. Hiding the loop light in front,
b. Modifying the Alienware™ head in front,
c. Covering any ventilation areas of the case,
d. Presenting the final version of the PC with opened side panels.


Well... that stifles the creativity a bit then doesnt it
